The United States, Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania have issued a joint declaration on increased security and defense cooperation. They reaffirm their strategic alliance and commit to deepening their cooperation to ensure security and stability in the region. They appreciate NATO's efforts to enhance deterrence and defense, including the forward presence in the eastern part of the Alliance. The four countries intend to reinforce and deepen their defense cooperation to promote regional security. They will focus on aligning security assistance and deterrence measures, as well as allocate necessary resources for defense spending. Regular meetings will be held to discuss defense and security priorities, including land, air, and maritime defense, border security, law enforcement, and national resilience. They also plan to explore areas for enhanced joint and regional cooperation in cyber defense, energy security, and critical infrastructure protection. The cooperation aims to strengthen NATO, promote regional cooperation, stability, and security, and address both conventional and unconventional threats.